caption: Delicious falafel at a reasonable price.  Variety of imported drinks that were very tasty.  Recommended if you're hungry on the wharf.
Delicious, affordable and has a social mission.  What is not to like?

When they closed at the beginning of the pandemic I was so afraid they weren't coming back and then they eventually came back and I've loved their falafel salad and their fries and then I came back today and it turns out they have a vegan shawarma.  And the thing is amazing. The same $5 as the salad, which is still wonderful, but I was in total foodgasm mode the entire time I was eating it which my companion can attest to. So I absolutely plan to come back and I will have to really think about whether I still want salads or whether I want this. Oh and also! They will now sell you a bag of just falafels for three bucks. Which was perfect, for snacking, and for introducing my companion to falafels being someone different from just chickpeas. He approves us both the falafels and the shawarma ;)  (My current problem is that I'm sitting here very very tempted to eat more fries or falafel but I am entirely too full. That's shawarma was really filling!)  PS: the photo of the sandwich is about 2/3 through eating it what I was able to focus on something other than eating it and remembered I wanted to take a picture
Great food, great cause! Their GF falafel is delicious, and they're za'taar fries are to-die-for. They had very friendly staff at The Wharf location.
Great service and falafel sandwiches.

ABSOLUTELY AMAZING! I LOVE THEIR FOOD! THE FALAFEL IS COOKED TO PERFECTION! OUT OF SEVERAL FALAFEL PLACES I'VE BEEN OVER THE YEAR'S, THEIRS IS THE BEST! IT LITERALLY MELTS RIGHT IN YOUR MOUTH! I HAVE TAKEN SEVERAL FAMILY & FRIENDS FOR THE FIRST TIME & THEY LOVED IT AS WELL!
Best falafel sandwich I’ve ever had! The fries was also really delicious. I highly recommend this restaurant.
Great food, great service, great price, and quick! :)

I tried the Falafel inc in Virginia and it was so good. So when visiting DC, we had to try it again. The food is so fresh, the service is quick, and there's some outdoor seating. I hope they open up a location in Michigan soon!
Amazing food at an amazingly low price and supports refugees
Excellent value! We had the falafel bowl with hummus, a big salad! Zatar fries are great! Delicious! Healthy! Quick service.
This is my go to spot. Delicious food and even better prices

Holy cow, what an awesome place. The food is fresh (the falafel was made for us as we came in), delicious, and incredibly affordable. $5 will get you a falafel bowl, $3 will get you a side of fries, and $1 will get you some bomb hummus. The sauces were an awesome touch as well. (We loved that they had small to-go containers to bring them with you). The best part is that a portion of every sale helps refugees. If you're in the DC area, check this place out.

I find it incredible that one can get so much value for their dollar. The food is really good quality (great if you're vegetarian/ vegan!). Also in a beautiful new area in Washington DC. Photo is from down the block*
Probably the best bang for your buck if you're planning to eat in DC. Delicious falafel sandwiches for $4!

Unlike the beloved Georgetown locale, we received not French fries, but half fries. The sandwiches simply wiped the taste for falafel out of the palette. No quality control at this location, as to why no one was there at 1:09pm Saturday.
Excellent falafel bowl.  Fresh vegetables, pickles, and falafel with hummus for 5 bucks!  Not a sit down place, but great for takeout!  We ate outside on a bench
I enjoyed so much the sandwich and fries I bought today. Will go back to try their salads. Fair price and clean place.
Best Falafel in the city! So cheap too, don't know how they do it.
Good food. We tasted falafel and hummus, delicious. Really clean. Good and friendly service.
Omg the food is amazing!! Service is quick! The two guys working yesterday (Saturday) afternoon were so so so friendly too! Will deff be going back, can’t beat the price and amazing flavor!

This Falafel place is amazing. The falafel sandwich is the best that I have ever had and the fries are also pretty good. The staff is very friendly and the food is very reasonably priced. Also, some of the proceeds go to helping those in need. All around, great place!
Quick, good food and the prices are literally unbeatable for the area.
Delicious $3 falafel sandwich? Count me in
Delicious, I love this place. Wish there was seating but maybe that’s why it’s so cheap. Must try
Good value!

Went to one of their locations, they were closed despite saying they are open on Google. We told our friend who was from Virginia to recommend another place (we are from out of country) and he told us that he called the other location and they are open till 10. We arrive and they are also closed. This was on new year's eve and we wasted time going from one location to another only for both to be closed. Update your hours.
Stumbled upon this over the summer and it was delicious and incredibly cheap! Vegan friendly
The bowl was so good! The sauces are a really spicy but super good!
This place was not only tasty but also very cheap! Simple food with great flavor! Perfect quick bite :)
Tasty food.
Amazing prices especially for how delicious the food was!
Best falafel I’ve tried in USA
Delicious fast friendly and healthy. And great value, especially in comparison to all the other options at this location. Love this place. No seating though. You can eat in, but you'll be standing.

Excellent falafel at an appropriate price point! Honestly, the value for the quality of the food cannot be beat, especially in the Wharf area where everything is a fortune. If you work nearby or want a quick bite without breaking the bank, you can eat an entire falafel sandwich here for less than the price of ONE drip coffee at the nearby Blue Bottle coffee shop.
This was my first time there and it was so good. The food was very tasty and fresh. My sandwich cost $3 and it was satisfying.

Come here to eat! Sandwich and fries were a great choice at lunch time. The only regret I have is that I didn't try more sauces on my sandwich. Friendly people as soon as I walked in, too which always helps!
Short menu, good prices for a quick bite
Great Falfel and hummus. The only thing that I didn't like about this place is that there is nowhere to sit and eat your Falafel
Falafel are above average but the sauces, hummas and fries were excellent. Highly recommend the Habibi sauce.

$4 falafel bowls? Don't mind if I do!  I know, I thought there was some type of catch but there isn't! This is the BEST falafel bowl for the buck! It comes with like 7 falafels (at least that's what I counted). They're small but plenty.  Delicious, fast service, fresh and all made to order. Every meal you buy helps a refugee in need. Win win.  Seriously amazing prices and food! Perfect to grab and sit down on the water area. You cannot beat the quality and quantity for that cheap! Perfect for vegetarians/vegans. You can add hummus to your bowl for a little extra. Everything's great! Def a must if you're in the area and don't eat fish lol!
Good place, wish there were tables and chairs to sit and eat. Cheap and good food but.
Best flafel in dc 😍
Honestly, you can't beat the price and the sauces are divine. I loved my salad I got and plan on going back.
Will be one of my favorites when in town
Tasty but messy sandwich
Tasty falafels with delish middle eastern sauces to match. Zaatar fries are recommended as well. The menu has just a few options but they are all good.
Amazing Falafel for an great price.
If I could eat here everyday I would! Very gluten-free friendly and delicious! Love all the sauces, hummus, falafel and pickles! Prices are excellent!!! Don't hesitate to try this place!!
Best deal in town for the best cause! You can’t beat a $3 fresh falafel sandwich. The location alone is worth it. Don’t forget to try all the sauces!
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente
Amazing amazing food with incredible prices and a great community project behind. I hope they open one in Miami soon!
The best Falafel in DC with a cause and purpose I will always support them!
This guy had very bad service and he had bad attitude with me and  I like this place I like the food but I cant back any more in this  place because this guy he is very bad I am sorry falafel ink .
Great food at a great price! You can’t find any other deal this good at the Wharf. Very filling bowl with falafel for $5. Haven’t seen that for years
Cannot beat the prices, line moves fast and food is good.
My favorite new restaurant
Cheap, delicious, simple food. The Habibi sauce is unreal!  No indoor seating, but walk over to the waterfront to find a public table or bench.

Love the cause. Proceeds go to refugees in need. Reasonable pricing and great sides. I'm afraid the main attraction leaves a lot to be desired. Falafel is bad. Wanted it to be better. GT location I remember being a lot better quality.
Amazing food at amazing prices!  We got our food very quickly, and WOW, was it delicious and authentic!  And all in a good cause, so you can’t beat it :)
Great filling food for a great price. Highly recommend. Price is amazing for DC.
Falafel sandwich with hummus was top notch and the fries were fantastic.
Wonderful food and great staff! I can’t wait to come back.
Holy smokes, seriously delicious and I'm still in shock from the awesome price. I hope these guys spread all over DC!!
Great falafel. The staff is friendly and you can't beat the prices.
Good food.and affordable in DC
I've lived all over the Middle East and Falafel  Inc is by far the most authentic falafel sandwich I've found in DC yet. Tastes just like I'm back in Amman!

I had an unpleasant experience at Falafel Inc. when I requested a hummus bowl instead of a falafel bowl, as I am unable to eat falafel. I was told that could be done. I also requested no tabbouleh as I am gluten free. The person at the counter initially complied but was then extremely rude when I asked for an extra spoonful of hummus. I pointed out that I was not receiving falafel or tabbouleh and asked for substitution of extra humus instead. The counter person suggested I go buy a tub of hummus if I wanted more and then told me he doesn't do customizations. I was already holding the bowl in my hands and had paid for it. He offered to refund my money rather than accommodating a customer by spooning in an additional dollop of hummus. I cant tell you about the quality of the falafel, but the fries were excellent. I must say- and this is not sour grapes- the hummus was not good quality. I eat LOTS of hummus and this was watery and weak. So, I guess I was better off that the rude counter person didn't accommodate my request.
Quick and inexpensive - $3 for a sandwich is hard to beat (although if you’re hungry you’ll want 2 for lunch).
The zatar fries are the best. Sandwich was good too. Take note of the sauces to be sure you like what comes on it.
Very tasty food, very cheap, and fast! Also the money goes to a good cause. Very good experience
The food here is fresh and reasonably priced. The salad bowl looks refreshing and healthy.
Food was great, large portions and you can't beat the prices (especially at the Wharf)
Fantastic food, have had the bowl and pita and both are great, especially for the price. The ingredients go great together and are filling.
Great food!

I've been to Falafel Inc in Georgetown before, and I really liked it there. This one didn't have a line though which was great (might have had to do with the dreary weather when I went), and I walked right in, gave my order, paid, and got my food basically instantaneously. The downside of this though is that the falafels aren't fresh right out of the fryer, and mine tasted a bit stale. They weren't crispy nor light like the ones I had at the one in Georgetown. I was quite disappointed actually because they were so good before. They have all the sauces still though at this location which is good. There's no seating inside but there are umbrellas and tables to stand at outside! Also, I have no idea how they make profit because the food is so cheap; my bowl was $4.40 including tax!
Awesome falafels for unbelievably low prices... dont forget the different sauces...
Very good falafel place. Fries are great too. Caution: coke can costs $3 here.
The falafel is quite good and food enough.  The focus on the price of the product and not the product may or may not be a good idea.  The tabbouleh  is a bargain at $3 but the tabbouleh was not good.
Great place for falafel sandwiches and bowls on a budget! Their chips and zaatar are amazing! All the food is made fresh on site. The red sauce is a must try for those who like it spicy!
Located in the scenic wharf district, this place has unbeatable prices and tastes great, too!

A really nice and inexpensive place! Sandwhich was assembled within a few minutes and tasted great (only for $3 and $4 with hummus). They also have a variety of dips to eat with chips or to eat on their own. Also, there are sauces stationed against the wall that you can put in containers to take with you. The sauce range from creamy to spicy.
Amazing value at the Wharf! $3 Falafel & $3 seasoned fries were great!
I think the bowl for $4 was a better option than the sandwich for $3. The side of fries (+$4) were good, but the bowl prob would have been enough.
Cheap, Inexpensive but not filling.  Guess you could order 2 but then it gets expensive.  Will try again
Delicious and affordable food on the wharf. $3 pita sandwiches $4 salads. Can't beat that! This may be my new go to spot on the wharf!
Good price
Good falafel. Nice location
Amazing food..!!

The best Falafel ever in DC area! Their fries is really good as well. Lots of sauces, and all good. Try "Mazbout" sauce and if you like spicy, try the "Habibi" sauce.  The first Falafel Inc in Georgetown was clearly a success story, except that it is in a very busy street, and it's very small place, with no place to stand to eat your sandwich.  Now, this new location at Maine Ave solves this problem. The store is big, the space outside to eat is nice and you can get your sandwich and walk around the wharf.
(Translated by Google) Of the best and best and best of falafel in all America  (Original) من فضل واطعم واحسن فلافل في امريكا كلها
Seriously low prices for some solid food. I love vimto and was pleasantly surprised to see it here. Drinks are surprisingly expensive but they have to make money somehow.
Awesome falafel sandwiches. The fries are amazing as well. It was a little crowded in the evening, but it was worth the wait.

Good sandwich! I wish they had a description of the sauces they had. They should also have arrows on the floor to help guide the customer "traffic"; can be confusing for new customers. I would recommend this place and will come here again!
Love falafels

My family and I were visiting DC for spring break this week and happened across this restaurant. I ordered three bowls for us to share and promptly dropped one as soon as I walked out the door. The manager saw what happened and personally remade one for me, even though it was clearly my own clumsy fault and he didn't have to do that. My kids were hungry from a long day of walking around and sight seeing, so we definitely appreciated his awesome gesture. Great customer service, and the food was wonderful too. Highly recommend.

I’m always on the lookout for a good falafel. Today I tried the Falafel Bowl which was essentially a salad with falafel balls on top. They added numerous sauces and veggie items (a zingy red cabbage, a pungeant pickled item and more). The falafel balls were delicious. There were several crispy pita chips. Everything about this was tasty. It was so flavorful- maybe a little too flavorful (but I won’t ding them for that- just be advised- if you’re sensitive to spicy flavors or pickled items, then ask to have those items held off). This is a small shop, good for taking something to go and eating out on the wharf or at home. Next time I’ll try the sandwich with the pita. Also, the prices are unbeatable. I told the guy the place is underpriced and they could easily charge double.

I work on the Wharf and while I'm glad there are now a lot of options for lunch, I am so excited there is finally a delicious, cost effective choice for lunch. I got a bowl + hummus and fries and spent less than $9.  The falafel was fantastic and the garlic sauce a nice addition.  A+
Tremendous value! Great falafel for only $3. Service is fast and staff is friendly. Fantastic place for a quick bite at The Wharf.
Unreal prices, mission and food!
Excited for this location! For those who live on the east side of DC, it makes it easier to get the best falafel in DC. Looking forward to this summer at the Warf and Falafel Inc.

Honestly, I didn't think they could duplicate the same great food from their Georgetown location, but they did! Falafel, Inc. has the best falafels in town. This location is brilliant and price still can't be beat.
Loved the food and concept.  I have traveled the world and this is the best falafel and it’s only $4
Great location. A little larger than the original but same great character and same delicious falafel at still $3 for a sandwich.
